<teaserTitle>Fig Bruschetta</teaserTitle>
<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>Another mediterranean favorite is Bruschetta - toasted white bread spread with tomato sauce and other delicacies such as goat cheese and figs.</p></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>Another mediterrenean favorite is Bruschetta - toasted white bread spread with tomato sauce and other delicacies such as goat cheese and figs.</p><p class="p--heading-2">Ingredients</p><ul><li>1/2 coles rustic baguette</li><li>1 tablespoon coles finest australian extra virgin olive oil</li><li>4 Fresh Figs, quartered</li><li>3 tablespoons finest red gum honey</li><li>16 slices goat cheese with italian black truffle</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><ul><li>Thinly slice the baguette</li><li>Drizzle with oil and bake at 180Â°c for 5-10 minutes or until golden and crunchy</li><li>Set aside to cool</li><li>Heat a non-stick pan over a medium heat</li><li>Dip figs cut-side down in honey and cook until honey has caramelised</li><li>Top each slice of bread with coles finest australian goats cheese rolled in italian black truffle, and a fig quarter then drizzle with remaining honey to serve.</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>The bruschetta should be served immediately, otherwise the delicious crispness is lost.</p></div></detailText>
